The `% placeholders.length` guard on line 68 prevents an out-of-bounds crash, but the user could momentarily see the wrong placeholder (e.g., index 3 in a new 4-item array starting from the 4th item instead of the 1st).

**Recommendation:** Add `setIndex(0)` at the top of the effect unconditionally, or at least when the placeholders reference changes.

**Severity:** Low (edge case, but sloppy).

---

### STYLE - Cycling Placeholder Vertical Alignment May Drift from Input Text

**File:** `/Users/anotonio.silva/antonio/lol/src/components/search_bar/search_bar.scss`, lines 84-101

```scss
.search-bar__cycling-placeholder {
  position: absolute;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  height: 100%;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  font-family: $font-family;
  font-size: $font-search;
  color: var(--text-400);
  pointer-events: none;
  // ...
}
```

The overlay uses `display: flex; align-items: center` on the full height of the wrapper. The `<input>` element uses `height: 100%` with no explicit `line-height` or padding. On most browsers, input text is vertically centered by default, so this will likely match. However, the alignment is coincidental rather than guaranteed -- different browsers and OS font rendering may place the input text baseline at a slightly different position than a flex-centered span.

**Recommendation:** Consider adding explicit `line-height` and `padding` to both the input and the cycling placeholder to guarantee pixel-perfect alignment, or test across target platforms to confirm. Since this is a Tauri app (primarily WebKit/Chromium), the risk is lower but worth verifying.

**Severity:** Low (cosmetic, may not manifest).

---

### GOOD - Proper Cleanup on Unmount

The cleanup function on lines 51-54 correctly clears both the interval and the pending timeout:

```tsx
return () => {
  clearInterval(interval);
  clearTimeout(timeout);
};
```

This handles the unmount-mid-transition case correctly. If the component unmounts between `setVisible(false)` and the timeout firing, the timeout is cleared and no state update on an unmounted component occurs. React 18+ handles this gracefully anyway, but the cleanup is still proper hygiene.

---

### GOOD - Accessibility

- `aria-hidden="true"` on the cycling placeholder span (line 199) correctly hides the decorative overlay from screen readers.
- The input retains `aria-label="Search commands"` (line 192), so screen readers have a meaningful label regardless of the visual placeholder.
- The native `placeholder` attribute is correctly removed when cycling is active (`hasCycling ? undefined : placeholder` on line 187), avoiding a double-text visual artifact.

---

### GOOD - pointer-events: none

The overlay span has `pointer-events: none` (line 94 in SCSS), ensuring clicks pass through to the input. Users can click anywhere in the search bar to focus the input even when the cycling placeholder is displayed.

---

### MINOR - className Construction

**File:** `/Users/anotonio.silva/antonio/lol/src/components/search_bar/search_bar.tsx`, line 198

```tsx
className={`search-bar__cycling-placeholder${cycling.visible ? '' : ' search-bar__cycling-placeholder--hidden'}`}
```

This works but is a long string interpolation. Consider a utility or at minimum a `const` for readability, especially since the project doesn't use a classnames library. Not a blocker.

---

### SUMMARY

| Issue | Severity | Verdict |
|-------|----------|---------|
| Array referential identity in useEffect deps | Critical (latent) | **Must fix** |
| FADE_DURATION (300ms) vs $transition-slow (250ms) mismatch | Medium | **Must fix** |
| Index not reset when placeholders array changes | Low | Should fix |
| Vertical alignment of overlay vs input text | Low | Verify visually |
| className readability | Nit | Optional |

**Verdict: Request changes.** The timing mismatch will cause a visible stutter during transitions, and the referential identity issue is a ticking time bomb. Both should be addressed before merge.

